lead_paragraph: Karrie Webb, a two-time player of the year, had eight birdies in a five-under-par 66 to lead after the first round of the L.P.G.A.'s Michelob Ultra Open at Williamsburg, Va. Webb has a one-shot lead over Jimin Kang. Annika Sorenstam continued to be baffled by the River Course at Kingsmill, and by her inconsistency, managing only one birdie in a two-over 73 on the 6,306-yard layout. In three previous visits to Kingsmill, Sorenstam's best finish was sixth, in 2003.
